cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with information theory and compression, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of probability theory suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of Blahut's algorithm suggests cs.MM (Multimedia), which often deals with compression and coding techniques.
